The independent schools in Scotland have an excellent record of academic excellence, and this continued in 2018 with another series of excellent exam results, as well as individual and collective success in sports, art, music and other initiatives of the whole community.
With more than 30,000 students in Scotland, these schools, represented by The Scottish Council of Independent Schools (SCIS), aim at providing the best service to their pupils and parents.
Independent schools seek to prepare their students for further and higher education, their chosen career and their place as world citizens.
As an educational sector that can design and implement a custom-made school curriculum, we see that modern languages remain popular and desirable subjects at the very heart of schools.
Nelson Mandela said: ‘ If you talk to someone in a language he understands, you reach his head.
When you talk to him in his own language, you reach his heart."
